      <div type="notes" xml:lang="eng">
	<p>This edition and translation is based on <ref target="bibl:Chandra1919">Chandra 1919–1920</ref>.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<ab>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	    sidhaṃ namo bhagavato <persName key="pers:Am-Śrīnegica">siri-negicasa</persName> pusa
	    <persName key="pers:Am-Kalika"><unclear>ka</unclear>likasa</persName>
	    <persName key="pers:Am-Harṣa">haṣasa</persName> bhariyaya ca catiyaput<unclear>ā</unclear>na ca
	  <lb n="2"/>
	    <persName key="pers:Am-Candramukha">mahācaṃdamukhasa</persName>
	    <persName key="pers:Am-Culacandramukha">culacaṃdamukhasa</persName> bālikaya
	    ca utariyasa nuṭhi ca haghaya bhalaha <gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="1"/>ghaya viya <choice><sic>sa</sic><corr>si</corr></choice> ru
	  <lb n="3"/>
	    <gap reason="lost" quantity="5" unit="character"/><persName key="pers:Am-Bala">balasa</persName> deyadhammaṃ pa<unclear>ti</unclear>ṭhapita
	    udha-paṭa
	</ab>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
	<p>Success! Adoration to the Blessed One! (This) upright slab placed
	(here) is the pious gift of <persName key="pers:Am-Kalika">Kalika</persName>,
	the son (pusa = putasa) of <persName key="pers:Am-Śrīnegica">Siri-Negica</persName>,
	and of the wife of <persName key="pers:Am-Harṣa">Harṣa</persName> and of
	<persName key="pers:Am-Candramukha">Candramukha the Elder</persName>
	and of <persName key="pers:Am-Culacandramukha">Candramukha the Younger</persName>,
	sons of <persName key="pers:Am-Catiya">Catiya</persName> and his daughter 
	[and the granddaughter of Utariya Gahā and Cula-haghā] and of 
	<persName key="pers:Am-Bala">Bala</persName>.</p>
      </div>
